# GitHub CODEOWNERS — controls who must review changes to which paths.
# https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositories-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# To make this load-bearing, also enable in GitHub repo settings:
#   Settings → Branches → Branch protection rules → main
#     ☑ Require a pull request before merging
#     ☑ Require approvals (1)
#     ☑ Require review from Code Owners
#     ☑ Restrict who can push to matching branches (optional, lets only
#       owner push directly; everyone else must PR)
#
# With those settings on, every PR needs a code-owner approval. The
# default rule below makes the repo owner the code owner for everything;
# the categories.json override delegates that one path to a collaborator.

# Default owner: everything not matched by a more specific rule below.
*                                @eric-ships

# Categories — collaborators can self-approve PRs that only touch this file.
# Add more usernames space-separated as additional collaborators are added.
/src/data/categories.json        @eric-ships
